description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a Registered Mental Health Nurse and/or Registered Nurse Learning Disability into the position of Team Leader on a male psychiatric intensive care unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have opportunity to use your clinical expertise working within a well-supported MDT who are dedicated to providing safe quality care for up to 10 male patients requiring a PICU care environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The patients accessing the ward are via referral where a more intensive support is required than can be provided within a usual acute ward setting. You will be supported to work within the PICU policies which includes the gatekeeping of referrals to ensure patients are cared for within an appropriate placement within least restrictive practice principles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will include the support of our staff both within the Willows Ward and wider teams via senior support as part of the unit coordination. You will be supported to utilise your skills within this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your role will consist of supporting the ward manager to lead a team of nursing staff on one of our Inpatient wards at the Wells Road Centre, promoting and maintaining high standards of care through communication, motivation, supervision and role modelling.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have the motivation, compassion and commitment to working in a PICU environment, providing professional leadership. You will take charge of a ward and deputise in the absence of the Ward Manager. Team Leaders will also take on the role of unit coordinator and have overall responsibility for ensuring the day to day management of the unit, including resource and incident management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Highbury Hospital provides comprehensive treatment pathways for both men with a diagnosis of learning disability and mental health issues and women with complex needs including enduring psychosis, trauma, personality disorder, offending behaviour, self-harm and substance misuse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Currently we have 5 established adult mental health inpatient wards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 female 16 bedded acute wards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 male 16 bedded acute wards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 male 10 bedded PICU&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have you the enthusiasm, and motivation to want to make a difference to the patients we care for?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be an expectation that you will act as a mentor / support and demonstrate procedures to and supervise qualified / unqualified staff and student nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We understand that you will want to develop your own unique skills and competences which we will help you to achieve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to provide clinical supervision and undertake appraisal systems for a group of staff as well as maintaining your own continuing professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential that you are able to work flexible hours, over 7 days a week, covering a 24 hour pattern. This is an exciting and challenging opportunity to work as part of a dynamic team within the Acute Care Pathway. You will be a member of and supported by your colleagues in the Acute Leadership Team. You will provide a visible point of contact to colleagues requiring guidance and support in the delivery of care and a contact point for liaison with other professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to find out more please call - 01159691300&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Charlotte Green, Acting Service Manager - ext 11074 or email charlotte.green@nottshc.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Steve Hill - Highbury Matron - ext 14959 or email steve.hill@nottshc.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*The closing date given is a guide. We reserve the right to close the post early once we have received a sufficient number of applicants, so we advise you to submit your application early to prevent disappointment. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*We will be requesting references by email.  Please ensure you include email addresses and contact numbers for your referees to avoid delay in the recruitment process.&lt;/p&gt;
